  "local_port": 60930,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "Dropping off a U-Haul at a different location involves a few straightforward steps. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n1. **Select the One-Way Rental Option**: When booking your U-Haul, make sure to choose the one-way rental option, which allows you to pick up the vehicle at one location and drop it off at a different location. \n\n2. **Confirm the Drop-off Location**: When making your reservation online or over the phone, specify the drop-off location. You can choose from the U-Haul locations available for one-way trips.\n\n3. **Check the Rental Agreement**: Review your rental agreement to confirm that it includes the alternate drop-off location and any fees associated with it.\n\n4. **Plan Your Drop-off Time**: Make sure you know the hours of operation for the drop-off location. Some locations may have specific hours, especially if they are smaller or operated by an individual.\n\n5. **Return the Vehicle**: When you arrive at the drop-off location, park the U-Haul in the designated area. Most locations will have a designated drop-off zone for rentals.\n\n6. **Complete the Check-in Process**: Depending on the location, you may be required to check in online or at a service counter. If you have a smartphone, U-Haul offers a mobile return option that allows you to complete the drop-off digitally.\n\n7. **Verify the Condition of the Vehicle**: Ensure that you take photos of the vehicle's condition before leaving, just in case there are any disputes regarding damages.\n\n8. **Return the Keys**: Follow the drop-off instructions provided by the location for returning the keys.\n\n9. **Receive Confirmation**: After completing the drop-off, ensure that you have a confirmation of the return, either via email or a printed receipt.\n\nIf you have any specific questions or issues while dropping off your U-Haul, it is always a good idea to contact U-Haul customer service or the drop-off location directly for assistance.",
